The paper presents a benchmark for training and evaluating robot navigation strategies that involve physical interaction with objects in indoor scenes. This involves simulating high fidelity visuals and physical dynamics of the robot and objects. This work is relevant to robotics (cs.RO), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and systems and control (cs.SY) as it involves developing and evaluating learning-based navigation solutions in cluttered environments.
